## Solution Complete: Diameter of Binary Tree

### Problem Analysis
- **Input**: Binary tree root node
- **Output**: Longest path between any two nodes (measured in edges)
- **Complexity Target**: O(n) time, O(h) space

### Strategy
The optimal approach uses a single DFS traversal that calculates height bottom-up while tracking the maximum diameter. At each node, the diameter passing through that node equals the sum of its left and right subtree heights. This avoids the O(n²) brute force approach of calculating height from every node separately.

### Solution Code
